  <text>
      <body>
         <entry xml:id="anqliton-1-ys"
            type="mainEntry"
            xml:lang="en"
            prev="#"
            next="#"
            source="Yalkut Shimoni">
            <form type="lemma">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">אנקליטון</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">ʾnqlyṭwn</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">anqliṭon</pron>
               <gramGrp>
                  <gram type="pos">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen">m.</gram>
               </gramGrp>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="anqliton-1-ys-1">
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>appeal [to higher authority]</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <quote>ἔκκλητον</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>בשר ודם תולין לו 
                     <app>
                        <lem>אנקלוטי</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#W">אנקליטון</rdg>
                     </app> מדוכוס לאפרכוס, מאפרכוס לאסטרטליטי. ואת בשביל שאין לך מי יתלה 
                     <app>
                        <lem>לך</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#W">לך אנקליטון</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#S Ven">לך אנקליטין</rdg>
                     </app> לא תעשה משפט.</quote>
                  <bibl>
                     <ref type="witness">Yalq 83</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">I 378: 82</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">דוכוס</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">אפרכוס</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">אסטרטליטי</ref>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>R. Yehuda be-R. Simon said: (Abraham pleaded thus:) ‘Even in the case of a human judge, an appeal can be made from the commander to the prefect and from the prefect to the governor; but you, because no appeal can be made from your judgment, will you not do justly? (cf. Freedman / Simon I 429)</quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note>= <bibl type="ancient">GenR 49,9 [II 510: 4; 511: 1]</bibl></note>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <note>Cf. GenR: <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa" target="anqliton.html">אנקליטון</ref></note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
               <bibl>
                  <title>Sperber (1984)</title>
                  <citedRange>48-49</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </ref>
         </entry>
